				<td colspan="2"><span>so did the poll. glad to be part of it. i know i'm not some uber bard, no longer in a guild, etc etc, but i have fun doing what i do.
<br />

<br />
which in my world is to pull, cc, add dps to the group, and dance circles around the group at the same time<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
so may i inquire why some of you bards out there feel the need for taunt? what situations do you have (other than last dual wielder standing - lazy monks) that create a need to pull/hold aggro?</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=44141><img border=0 src="http://www2.freepichosting.com/Images/421477286/2.jpg" /></a><br>
