			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: confused...<a name="52247"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 16 04 10:05 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've only experience situations that I wished I could pull aggro, but never hold it. Situations like when an enchanter's mezz breaks and it heads straight to the enchanter or when I pull 2 mobs and one of them goes screaming past the MA and rams into the mage/necro. Or when the cleric spams quick heal and an add breaks loose.
<br />

<br />
Usually, I wish I could have a way to gain instant aggro so I can use my plate wearing butt to shield the less able. I have no wish to be a full time tank, I'll leave that to more /disc capable classes, but I do wish I can pull aggro when it means saving someone else or if there are no other options. Rangers pull aggro faster than I can and they are a chain class. BLs grab it even faster and they are limited to leather. Bards get the AC benefit of plate but can't pull aggro when its needed.
<br />

<br />
I don't see taunt as a major issue though but deserving to be in the top 10, IMO.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
