			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: confused...<a name="52255"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 16 04 10:39 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The most OBVIOUS reason.. to aggro kite.
<br />

<br />
If we could establish snap aggro, we could kite triggered spawns and such without the need to rely soley (and hopefully) on  'songs that have aggro components' (debuffs, snares, AoE heals, etc). Think kiting the gargoyles in the TT encounter or the Gargantula spiderlings, etc. etc. Most utility would come (at the high end game anyhow) from being able to hold the attention of summoners without doing enough damage for them to start summoning.
<br />

<br />
There are also times when you don't have a 'better option' for a tank and keeping any meaningful aggro against DPS classes is not possible (4-man LDoNs being my most common personal encounter).
<br />

<br />
To be honest, it is nowhere NEAR being a 'need' issue, but it sure would be nice to have 'Manilow's Melody of Religious Country Rap' to inspire instant hatred (if for no other reason than to kite or occupy a critter long enough to buy time fer the healers to heal or the necros to FD or whatever). 
<br />

<br />
Of course, any kind of AoE taunt song would make us even more universally despised as 'bad bards' go into camp-stealing or kill-stealing situations. The combination of taunt AND FM has lots of potential for abuse. It would make splitting with bards (even more) insanely easy since you  would no longer have to worry about 'proximity aggro only' issues with those massive trains. Don't want to deal with a boss monster with guardians? Have a bard kite the whole zone to the other side with his new aggro song, then have a ranger (or whatever) pull the one you want out to the 'throng of groupies' (yes, I know we can already do this, but at least there is currently a measure of skill/risk involved).
<br />

<br />
It sure would make farmin,  factioning, and rounding up AoE swarms easier though (and much safer for spectators). The major disavantage would be that it would hog up a spell gem I have far better use for. To be honest, unless it was MAJOR hate generation (with a much higher success rate than melees currently enjoy), I doubt I would forego any of my spell gems for a 'taunt song' (especially seeing how well it works (or doesn't, as the case may be) for melees). And, as much as I hate to say it, it would be a major intrusion into the niche of the tank classes. Taunt is one of their class-defining abilities. We already have the ability to do far more overall. Taking their taunt is just overkill and would likely be unbalancing (not to mention infuriating to melees where taunt is so broken already). 
<br />

<br />
Creative use of what we already have is far more potent (IMO) than any additional situational song anyhow. If they were to put such a song in (and it wasn't ridiculously hard to get without a massive time-equipped guild), sure, I'd get it, but it would likely be yet another situational song of convenience I'd rarely (if ever) give up a spell gem to.
<br />

<br />
Might be a nifty addition to the &lt;L30 crowd though.
<br />

<br />
-Savidge Rhythums
<br />
-Quellious</span></td>
