				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: confused...<a name="52927"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 20 04 10:16 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>For low end Bards, I would say the biggest issues are...
<br />

<br />
1)  Fix the &quot;wears off&quot; bug.  
<br />

<br />
Before you get lvl 49 Selos, this one kills Bards all the time, and NOT because they are making a mistake.  Simply because their speed drops when it shouldn't.
<br />

<br />
2)  More LDoN points for missions.  
<br />

<br />
I know this is not a Bard-specific thing, but there are many LDoN vendor items that would be a godsend for young bards, but by the time you get the points, you aren't a young bard anymore.  A Primary equippable Lute, for example.  (Before LDoN, LotH was the most attainable one-- yeah right!)
<br />

<br />
3)  Replace lvl 3 Jig with?
<br />

<br />
SELF INVIS, of course!  Or if they think that is too soon for a Bard to have such an uber ability, then give us self invis when we get wind at lvl 11, and make Jig into a modest melee rune or damage shield.  Those are both things that we don't get until later in the game, that could be scaled back for level appropriateness, without really affecting game balance.
<br />

<br />
4)  Lose the &quot;Charm Gap&quot; (AND the &quot;Mez Gap&quot; around lvl 55ish...)
<br />

<br />
Not only should the lvl 64 Charm song have its cap raised, there needs to be one in between.  I don't see any reason why this class-defining ability should have to vanish after a certain level.
<br />

<br />
The gaps in Charm and Mez caps in the high 50s (the absolutely suckiest spot in the xp curve as well) Bards lose their ability to CC effectively.
<br />

<br />
5)  Fix the itemization issues for high end Bards, so they can actually GET upgraded instruments and equipment, so they can pass their old junk along to younger bards please.
<br />

<br />
As others have suggested, Bards really DO have it pretty good at lower levels.  By the time we can do LDoNs, we have Lull and Mez, and can pull and CC like a dream.  By lvl 26, we can solo as well as any other class in the game.  (Earlier, if one can master AE kiting).  For low-end raiding, our resists and overhaste make us very desirable.  Overall, we are doing just fine.
<br />

<br />
(As for taunting to get a mob off a Druid or Wizzie so they can Evac, why?  You can Mez or charm them!  But then, the reason you have to evac now is probably cause you suck, and can't pull or CC anyway!  :b )  Note:  I don't mean &quot;you&quot; the poster, rather, the Bard who thinks Taunt is going to save their group from wiping, lol.</span></td>
